chh.math.sets

Class Pair

  • java.lang.Object
    • chh.math.sets.Set
      • chh.math.sets.Pair
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    OrderedPair, Singleton

    public class Pair
extends Set
    The Axiom of Pair: Given two sets x and y, there exists a set {x,y} that contains exactly them both. The order of these elements is not relevant; that is, (new Pair(a,b)).equals(new Pair(b,a)), and (new Pair(a,b)).equals(new Pair(b,a)) both return true.
    Version:
    2013.07.26
    Author:
    Christopher H. Harvey

      • includes

        public boolean includes(Set x)
        Returns whether this Set has the specified Set as a subset. The set x is a subset of a set y exactly when "all the elements of x are in y", that is: for all sets t, if t is an element of x then t is an element of y. Although there is a Subset class, some Set objects may have the property of being a subset of this one without being an instance of the Subset class.
        Specified by:
        includes in class Set
        Parameters:
        x - the specified set
        Returns:
        true if x is a subset of this set

      • isEmpty

        public boolean isEmpty()
        Returns whether this Set has no elements. A set y is empty exactly when: for all sets t, t is not an element of y. Although there is a EmptySet class, some Set objects may have the property of being empty without being an instance of the EmptySet class. A Pair is always nonempty.
        Specified by:
        isEmpty in class Set
        Returns:
        false
        See Also:
        EmptySet

      • isInductive

        public boolean isInductive()
        Returns whether this set is inductive. A set y is inductive iff:
        1. y contains an EmptySet
        2. For every element t in y, y contains the SuccessorSet of t.
        Although there is a InductiveSet class, some Set objects may have the property of being inductive without being an instance of the InductiveSet class. No Pair objects are inductive.
        Specified by:
        isInductive in class Set
        Returns:
        false
